Some thoughts:

* The result about composition of fibrations holds in any 2-category with co=
mma objects and 2-pullbacks, not just Cat. (Think of the Chevalley criterion=
  for fibrations.)

* By duality on 2-cells it thus also applies to opfibrations, and hence to b=
ifibrations.

* It is bifibration structure that gives you the left adjoints you ask for.

* For the right adjoints, look at the dual 2-category, where your fibrations=
  become bifibrations.

Hence it seems to me that your conjectures are all true, and even generalize=
  widely.

Steve.

